comment_zero_shot:
```c
// BUG: Potential use-after-free vulnerability
// The function ff_lpc_end() is supposed to free the windowed_samples array, 
// but the pointer arithmetic (&s->windowed_samples) is incorrect. 
// It should be (&s->windowed_samples) instead of (&s->windowed_samples - 1).
// This could lead to undefined behavior if the caller still accesses the freed memory.
```

Corrected code:
```c
av_cold void ff_lpc_end ( LPCContext * s ) { av_freep ( & s->windowed_samples ) ; }
```
